  <data-orientation>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{B1FEEEF1-E590-401E-845F-B48DF39440C7}' />
      <desc>Identifies which assets are truly outperforming the market and which are lagging, regardless of their nominal price. It clearly highlights the massive growth alpha provided by Nvidia compared to the flatter trajectory of local financials.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{C3A8A1F9-3060-4CB1-BCC0-30A72548586F}' />
      <desc>Helps the board identify &quot;danger zones.&quot; An asset in the bottom-right (High Risk, Low Return) is a candidate for divestment, while assets in the top-left (Low Risk, High Return) are candidates for increased capital allocation.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{BA64B48D-8E41-470F-B04D-DCE49EB47CA8}' />
      <desc>Prevents &quot;unintentional bias.&quot; If a high-growth stock like Nvidia has doubled in value, it may now represent a larger portion of the portfolio than originally intended. This chart signals when it is time to &quot;trim the winners&quot; to protect against a single-point-of-failure.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{B8305776-9A36-4525-85B9-8DD3722F4085}' />
      <desc>The primary goal of this dashboard is to provide a comprehensive, real-time view of the portfolio’s health, comparing high-growth global technology assets against stable South African market leaders. It is designed to help decision-makers identify over-concentration, evaluate risk-adjusted returns, and understand the impact of macro-economic volatility on total asset value.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
  </data-orientation>
</workbook>
